> Because I see the changes will only affect the `_ingestionSchemaValidator` within `SegmentIndexCreationDriverImpl` which has no usages, and some data generation tools.

Also I don't see how this change is helping. Comment from above: `Because I see the changes will only affect the _ingestionSchemaValidator within SegmentIndexCreationDriverImpl which has no usages, and some data generation tools.` 
Is this the main line of change in this PR? Everything else doesn't seem relevant.
```
if (dest != PinotDataType.JSON) {
          value = standardize(column, value, dest.isSingleValue());
        }
```
And you shouldn't need this with jsonFormat.

@Jackie-Jiang 
Maybe we can make new data types supporting null value by default?

Also for TIMESTAMP, I feel both deterministic value or current timestamp can be default null value.
